00:36:09,447 --> 00:36:10,675
Mai?

544
00:36:16,654 --> 00:36:18,349
Daddy, over here!

545
00:36:18,456 --> 00:36:20,890
I think I know where Mai went.

546
00:36:31,636 --> 00:36:32,967
[Gasp]

547
00:36:33,071 --> 00:36:34,129
Mai?

548
00:36:34,239 --> 00:36:35,536
Mai!

549
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:36,572
Wake up!

550
00:36:36,674 --> 00:36:37,538
Wake up.

551
00:36:38,243 --> 00:36:40,177
[Moaning]

552
00:36:44,249 --> 00:36:47,776
<i>Wake up, Mai! Right now!</i>

553
00:36:48,586 --> 00:36:51,248
You have no business
sleeping in this place.

554
00:36:52,924 --> 00:36:54,255
<i>How come he's gone?</i>

555
00:36:54,359 --> 00:36:55,849
<i>How come who's gone?</i>

556
00:37:00,265 --> 00:37:02,256
Tell me who you lost.

557
00:37:02,367 --> 00:37:03,925
A big Totoro was here with me.

558
00:37:04,035 --> 00:37:07,129
A big one like
what's in our picture books?

559
00:37:07,238 --> 00:37:08,136
Mm-hmm.

560
00:37:08,239 --> 00:37:10,764
<i>And I climbed up on top of him,</i>

561
00:37:10,875 --> 00:37:14,504
<i>and he was furry,
and he had a big mouth,</i>

562
00:37:14,612 --> 00:37:18,173
and there was a little one
and one this big

563
00:37:18,283 --> 00:37:21,343
and a great big one sleeping by himself.

564
00:37:21,452 --> 00:37:22,942
Uh-huh?

565
00:37:23,054 --> 00:37:26,512
Hello! Is anybody in there?

566
00:37:27,692 --> 00:37:28,624
Well, I'll be.

567
00:37:28,726 --> 00:37:30,523
What a great hiding place.

568
00:37:30,628 --> 00:37:34,064
Daddy, Mai told me
she saw a big Totoro.

569
00:37:34,165 --> 00:37:35,757
A real one?

570
00:37:35,867 --> 00:37:36,765
Mm-hmm.

571
00:37:36,868 --> 00:37:37,994
This way.

572
00:37:41,940 --> 00:37:43,601
Ha ha!

573
00:37:45,877 --> 00:37:47,435
Hey, give me a chance.

574
00:37:52,884 --> 00:37:54,044
Here?

575
00:37:54,152 --> 00:37:55,380
Mmm. Mm-hmm.

576
00:37:55,486 --> 00:37:57,977
He was by the big tree
a little while ago.

577
00:37:58,089 --> 00:38:00,557
I don't see how he could've escaped.

578
00:38:01,426 --> 00:38:03,917
<i>Mai! Mai, come back!</i>

579
00:38:14,672 --> 00:38:16,003
Ha ha ha!

580
00:38:16,107 --> 00:38:18,302
Ha ha ha ha!

581
00:38:18,409 --> 00:38:19,341
Stop laughing!

582
00:38:19,444 --> 00:38:22,413
I really saw him. I m not lying.

583
00:38:23,014 --> 00:38:24,038
I'm not lying.

584
00:38:33,024 --> 00:38:34,423
Mai.

585
00:38:34,892 --> 00:38:36,655
You don't believe me.

586
00:38:36,761 --> 00:38:39,252
<i>Mm-hmm. That's where you're wrong.</i>

587
00:38:39,364 --> 00:38:42,060
<i>l believe you're being
completely truthful about this.</i>

588
00:38:42,166 --> 00:38:45,932
But I also believe that you met
the king of the forest.

589
00:38:46,037 --> 00:38:48,028
Meeting him is a sign of good luck.

590
00:38:48,673 --> 00:38:52,871
<i>There's no guarantee
you'll see him all the time.</i>

591
00:38:52,977 --> 00:38:55,468
<i>We'll have to pay our respects.</i>

592
00:38:55,580 --> 00:38:56,444
Where do we find him?

593
00:38:56,547 --> 00:38:59,311
Miss Mai will find him for us.

594
00:39:13,398 --> 00:39:14,387
Oh!

595
00:39:15,166 --> 00:39:17,726
<i>Ohh, Mai, you're getting heavier
by the minute.</i>

596
00:39:17,835 --> 00:39:19,632
Daddy, the camphor tree.

597
00:39:20,538 --> 00:39:22,802
What a beautiful tree.

598
00:39:30,148 --> 00:39:32,013
I found it.

599
00:39:32,316 --> 00:39:33,544
<i>You sure that's the one?</i>

600
00:39:33,651 --> 00:39:34,811
Uh-huh.

601
00:39:34,919 --> 00:39:37,479
What are you waiting for, Daddy?
Hurry up.

602
00:39:44,595 --> 00:39:46,654
<i>The hole's not there anymore,</i>

603
00:39:47,832 --> 00:39:49,766
but I'm sure this is where it was.

604
00:39:49,867 --> 00:39:51,357
You're positive it is?

605
00:39:51,469 --> 00:39:52,731
Mm-hmm.

606
00:39:52,837 --> 00:39:54,828
<i>The opening's completely disappeared.</i>

607
00:39:54,939 --> 00:39:57,601
Remember, you can see him
only when he wants you to.

608
00:39:57,709 --> 00:40:00,371
Will we see him? I want to meet him.

609
00:40:01,179 --> 00:40:03,977
<i>You never can tell.
If we're lucky enough.</i>

610
00:40:05,283 --> 00:40:07,080
What a beautiful tree it is.

611
00:40:07,685 --> 00:40:11,781
This tree's been here,
well, since before anyone can remember.

612
00:40:11,956 --> 00:40:14,117
<i>You know, a long time ago,</i>

613
00:40:14,225 --> 00:40:17,456
Man and trees were the best of friends.

614
00:40:18,796 --> 00:40:23,563
<i>It's actually because of this tree
that I decided to buy our house,</i>

615
00:40:23,668 --> 00:40:26,102
<i>and Mommy will like it, too.</i>

616
00:40:26,204 --> 00:40:29,571
Let's thank the king of the forest
and get back for lunch.

617
00:40:29,674 --> 00:40:32,370
I have to meet Michiko after lunch.

618
00:40:32,477 --> 00:40:33,569
<i>I'm coming, too.</i>

619
00:40:33,678 --> 00:40:35,703
Attention!

620
00:40:36,047 --> 00:40:38,038
Thank you for all you've done for Mai.

621
00:40:38,149 --> 00:40:40,709
Please protect her forever.

622
00:40:40,818 --> 00:40:43,548
